  },
  {
    "line": 3,
    "content": "This section presents the comprehensive experimental results of the A* algorithm performance evaluation across four distinct scenarios. A total of 200 test cases were executed, with detailed analysis of search time, node expansion, path length, and success rates under varying environmental conditions."
  },
  {
    "line": 4,
    "content": ""
  },
  {
    "line": 5,
    "content": "\\subsection*{Scenario A: Impact of Map Size on Algorithm Performance}"
  },
  {
    "line": 6,
    "content": ""
  },
  {
    "line": 7,
    "content": "The first scenario investigates how the computational complexity of A* scales with increasing problem space dimensions. Five map sizes were tested: 10×10, 20×20, 50×50, 100×100, and 200×200, with each configuration repeated 10 times to ensure statistical reliability."
  },
  {
    "line": 8,
    "content": ""
