  {
    "line": 12,
    "content": "\\caption{Impact of map size on A* algorithm performance. The dual-axis chart shows search time (left axis, blue line) and expanded nodes (right axis, red line) as functions of map dimensions. Search time increases from approximately 0.05 ms for 10×10 maps to 1.64 ms for 200×200 maps, while expanded nodes grow from 9.4 to 479.7. This exponential growth pattern demonstrates the computational complexity inherent in larger search spaces.}"
