  {
    "line": 14,
    "content": "\\end{figure}"
  },
  {
    "line": 15,
    "content": ""
  },
  {
    "line": 16,
    "content": "The results reveal a clear exponential relationship between map size and both search time and node expansion. For the smallest map (10×10), the algorithm achieved an average search time of 0.049 ms with 9.4 expanded nodes. As the map size increased to 200×200, the search time escalated to 1.641 ms with 479.7 expanded nodes on average. This 33-fold increase in search time and 51-fold increase in node expansion illustrates the fundamental computational challenges of pathfinding in larger environments. The consistent performance characteristics across all map sizes indicate that the algorithm maintains its efficiency properties despite the increased problem complexity."
  },
  {
    "line": 17,
    "content": ""
  },
  {
    "line": 18,
    "content": "\\subsection*{Scenario B: Heuristic Function Comparison}"
  },
  {
    "line": 19,
    "content": ""
  },
