  },
  {
    "line": 31,
    "content": "\\caption{Comparison of three heuristic functions in A* algorithm. The grouped bar chart displays the average number of expanded nodes for each heuristic function. Manhattan distance achieves the best performance with 40.0 nodes, followed by Euclidean distance with 153.7 nodes, and diagonal distance with 244.1 nodes. These results validate the theoretical understanding that more consistent heuristics lead to superior search efficiency.}"
