    "content": "\\caption{Impact of obstacle density on A* algorithm performance. The dual-axis chart shows search time (left axis, blue line) and success rate (right axis, green line) as functions of obstacle density. Search time remains relatively stable (0.11-0.43 ms) across densities from 0\\% to 40\\%, while success rate decreases from 100\\% at lower densities to 90\\% at 50\\% obstacle density. This demonstrates the algorithm's robustness in constrained environments.}"
