    "line": 95,
    "content": "Future research could explore the combination of A* with other optimization techniques. Weighted A*, which uses a weighted heuristic $f(n) = g(n) + w \\cdot h(n)$ with $w > 1$, trades optimality for speed and could be valuable for applications where near-optimal solutions are acceptable. Anytime algorithms that provide progressively better solutions over time could be useful for time-constrained applications."
