    "line": 9,
    "content": "The results from Scenario A demonstrate a clear exponential relationship between map size and computational cost. As the map dimensions increased from $10 \\times 10$ to $200 \\times 200$, the search time escalated from 0.049 ms to 1.641 ms, representing a 33-fold increase. Simultaneously, the number of expanded nodes grew from 9.4 to 479.7, a 51-fold increase. This exponential growth pattern reflects the fundamental nature of grid-based pathfinding: larger maps contain more cells that must potentially be evaluated during the search process."
