    "line": 11,
    "content": "The theoretical basis for this observation lies in the computational complexity of A*. While A* is more efficient than uninformed search algorithms, its worst-case complexity remains exponential in the branching factor and solution depth. In grid-based environments with eight-directional movement, the branching factor is 8, and the solution depth increases with map size. However, the use of an admissible heuristic function significantly prunes the search space, preventing the algorithm from exploring all possible nodes. The exponential growth observed in our experiments is substantially mitigated compared to uninformed search, demonstrating the practical value of heuristic guidance."
