  {
    "line": 21,
    "content": "Furthermore, the informativeness of a heuristic—its ability to accurately estimate the remaining cost to the goal—directly influences the number of nodes that must be expanded. Manhattan distance provides a tighter lower bound on the actual cost to reach the goal in grid-based environments, causing the algorithm to prioritize nodes that are closer to the goal more effectively. This results in a more focused search that expands fewer nodes overall."
