    "line": 29,
    "content": "This robustness can be attributed to the algorithm's fundamental design. A* explores nodes in order of their estimated total cost to the goal, ensuring that it finds the optimal path whenever one exists. Obstacles do not fundamentally change the algorithm's behavior; they simply reduce the number of valid moves available at each node. The algorithm adapts naturally to these constraints by exploring alternative paths."
