    "content": "The linear relationship validates the theoretical understanding of A* efficiency. In an optimal scenario with a perfect heuristic, the algorithm would expand only the nodes along the optimal path. While our heuristics are not perfect, they are sufficiently informative to ensure that the number of expanded nodes scales approximately linearly with the solution path length. This is a significant advantage over uninformed search algorithms, which would expand nodes exponentially with solution depth."
